Boil a full kettle. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @rigatoni pasta{180%grams} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it from sticking together.

== Broccoli and Prep ==

Meanwhile, halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%grams} stems lengthways.

When there are 5 mins left of pasta cooking time remaining, add the broccoli to the pan and cook for the remaining time.

While the pasta cooks, peel and grate the @garlic{3%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop both the @olives{30%grams} and @capers{15%grams}.

== Chicken Puttanesca ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%grams} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Stir-fry the garlic and @chilli flakes{1%pinch} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), until fragrant, ~{30%secs}.

Stir the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}, olives, capers, @sugar{1%tsp for the sauce} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce into the pan. Simmer until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%mins}.

== Final Assembly ==

Once the sauce has thickened, lower the heat to medium and stir through the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%grams}. Cook for ~{1-2%mins}.

Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, or a pinch of @?sugar{} if you feel it needs it. Add a splash of @?water{} if the sauce is a little too thick.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the sauce is ready, add the cooked rigatoni, broccoli and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} to the pan. Stir and toss well to combine.

== To Serve ==

Share your Puttanesca style pasta between your serving bowls.

Sprinkle over the remaining half Italian style cheese. Enjoy!